Meanwhile, 2010 World Cup winners and reigning European champions Spain have fallen out of the top 10 in FIFA's rankings for the first time since 2007.

World Cup winners Germany is still No 1 ahead of Argentina, Colombia, Belgium and the Netherlands.

The only change in the top 10 is that Italy rise two places up to 10th, while Spain drop one spot to 11th.

None of the elite teams played in the last month, but games played earlier in the four-year cycle of results lost ranking value.

